This paper deals with the intersection of computer security and human-computer interaction, as it analyzes the behavior of users who seek anonymity through the use of Tor on a user-generated content site. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CY (Computer Science and Game Theory), which deals with the intersection of computer science and social sciences. 

The paper also deals with issues of online privacy and security, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). 

The analysis of user behavior and contributions to Wikipedia could also fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering), as it involves the study of online communities and the development of software tools to manage them. 

Finally, the paper also touches on issues of user experience and interface design, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
